org.intermine.neo4j.metadata

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.intermine.neo4j.metadata.Model

  • public class Model
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes a Neo4j graph data model. It gives access to various NodeType and RelType nodes and their relationships within the metagraph. Metagraph structure is described at https://github.com/intermine/neo4j/blob/dev/metadata.md .

    You can generate an instance of the Model class for a given Neo4j database by calling Neo4jSchemaGenerator.getModel() method. An instance of Model class provides a number of methods to query the data model. These methods can be used to query properties of nodes and relationships and to query how nodes are related to each other.

    Author:
    Yash Sharma
